Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.etree

Class EventTree<E extends Event>

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.etree.EventTree<E>
Type Parameters:
E - the type of event in this tree
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
BranchingEventTree
public class EventTree<E extends Event> extends Object implements Serializable
An event tree is a stateless data structure used to efficiently determine which events have preconditions satisfied in a given state.

The parent EventTree class is used the empty tree and for leaf nodes which contain events but not branches. Most event tree are branching events trees.

Author:
Stephen G. Ware

  • Method Details

    • getBranches

      public static ImmutableSet<Value> getBranches(Expression expression)
      Returns a set of all possible values that a given expression could have. If the expression given is of type boolean, this method returns {false, true}. If the expression is of type number, this method throws an exception, since there are infinitely many possible values. Otherwise, this method assumes the expression given is a fluent, and it returns all possible values of that fluent's type (including unknown if the fluent is of type entity).
      Parameters:
      expression - the expression for which all possible values are wanted
      Returns:
      a set of possible values the expression could evaluate to

    • getBranch

      public EventTree<E> getBranch(Value value)
      Event trees branch based on the value of their expression in some state. This method is used to get the branch of the tree for which the expression has the given value. When this method is called with null as its argument, it will return the irrelevant branch if one exists. If this tree has no branches for the given value, this method returns null.
      Parameters:
      value - the value of the tree's expression in some state
      Returns:
      the branch corresponding to the tree's expression have that value
